               <p>1364. <persName id="def1-1364-18360509" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1364-18360509" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1364-18360509" type="surname" value="PRICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1364-18360509" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN PRICE</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18360509-1364-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18360509-1364-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18360509-1364-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18360509-cd-206" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360509-1364-offence-1 t18360509-cd-206"></join>18th of April</rs>, 1 half-crown, 2 shillings, and 1 sixpence, the monies of <persName id="t18360509-name-1443" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1443" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1443" type="surname" value="LUCEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1443" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1443" type="occupation" value="lighterman"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360509-1364-offence-1 t18360509-name-1443"></join>William Lucey</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360509-name-1444" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1444" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1444" type="surname" value="LUCEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1444" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM LUCEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a lighterman, and live in East-lane. On the 18th of April, I was in the pit at Astley's theatre—the prisoner stood up behind me—I was standing on the sear, and he on the ground—I felt his right-hand, rifling my left pocket—he had not spoken to me before—I left both his hands at my left pocket—I had about 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in silver in it—I had counted it in the morning—I had spent some after, but I deducted that—I was quite sober—the prisoner made two or three attempts at my pocket, and the money dropped from his hand, which I felt fall in my pocket—I imagine he had a five-shilling-piece in his hand, as I heard it drop in my pocket—I at last lost about 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—after the fourth attempt I put my right hand to my pocket, and when he found I was suspicious of him, he put his hand over my shoulder, and spoke about the performance—I then charged him with it, and he was taken—there was some property</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183605090257"></xptr>
               <p>found on him, but I cannot say whether it was mine—he might have dropped it—when I recounted my money, I missed four or five shillings.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Can you tell what coins that was la? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I cannot—it was in silver—there was a great crowd in front of me in the theatre.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360509-name-1445" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1445" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1445" type="surname" value="GREEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-1445" type="given" value="MARK WILLIAM"></interp>MARK WILLIAM GREEN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 28.) the prosecutor charged the prisoner with putting his hand into his pocket, but not with stealing any thing—I found nine sovereigns, one half-crown, and 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., on the prisoner.</p>
